- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is likely because the paper deals with integer vectors and combinatorial optimization problems.
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is likely because the paper discusses polynomial-time computable balancing of conflicting costs.
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is likely because the paper deals with multi-objective optimization problems and approximations.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is likely because multi-objective optimization is a common problem in AI and the paper proposes solutions using degree theory.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is likely because the paper proposes algorithms for balancing combinations of solutions in multi-objective optimization.
